0abruptly%20resigned%20on%20March%209%2C%202024.%20Photo%3A%20eci.gov.in%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20the%20vacancy%20which%20came%20to%20be%20filled%20by%20Goel%20was%20created%20on%20May%2015%2C%202022.%20Goel%20was%20due%20to%20retire%20from%20the%20Indian%20Administrative%20Service%20on%20December%2031%2C%202022%2C%20but%20he%20requested%20voluntary%20retirement%20on%20personal%20grounds%20on%20November%2018%2C%202022%2C%20and%20it%20was%20approved%20on%20the%20very%20same%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20a%20two-judge%20Bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%C2%A0%3Ca%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22internal%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fsupreme-court-dismisses-pil-seeking-quashing-of-appointment-of-arun-goel-as-election-commissioner%2F%5C%22%3Edismissed%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0a%20public%20interest%20litigation%20filed%20by%20the%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR)%20seeking%20to%20quash%20Goel%E2%80%99s%20appointment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20matter%20of%20practice%2C%20the%20commission%20comprises%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20two%20election%20commissioners.%20Even%20before%20Goel%E2%80%99s%20resignation%2C%20there%20was%20one%20vacancy%20in%20the%20commission%20with%20the%20retirement%20of%20Anup%20Chandra%20Pandey%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fdid-arun-goel-express-his-dissent-within-the-ec-e-a-s-sarma-asks-president-to-probe%5C%22%3EDid%20Arun%20Goel%20Express%20His%20Dissent%20Within%20the%20EC%3F%20E.A.S.%20Sarma%20Asks%20President%20to%20Probe%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EHow%20CEC%20and%20ECs%20are%20appointed%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20Article%20324(2)%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20shall%20consist%20of%20a%20CEC%20and%20such%20number%20of%20other%20ECs%2C%20if%20any%2C%20as%20the%20President%20of%20India%20may%20from%20time%20to%20time%20fix%20and%20the%20appointment%20of%20a%20CEC%20and%20other%20ECs%20shall%2C%20subject%20to%20the%20provisions%20of%20any%20law%20made%20in%20that%20behalf%20by%20the%20Parliament%2C%20be%20made%20by%20the%20President%20of%20India.%3Cb%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUntil%20very%20recently%2C%20there%20was%20no%20law%20laying%20down%20the%20procedure%20for%20the%20appointment%20of%20CECs%20and%20ECs%2C%20and%20thus%20it%20was%20the%20sole%20prerogative%20of%20the%20Union%20executive%20to%20appoint%20CECs%20and%20ECs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOriginally%2C%20the%20commission%20had%20only%20a%20CEC.%20It%20was%20on%20October%2016%2C%201989%2C%20that%20the%20President%20of%20India%2C%20in%20exercise%20of%20his%20powers%20under%20Clause%202%20of%20Article%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.constitutionofindia.net%2Farticles%2Farticle-324-superintendence-direction-and-control-of-elections-to-be-vested-in-an-election-commission%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E324%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20fixed%20the%20number%20of%20ECs%20as%20two.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%20on%2C%20on%20October%2016%2C%201989%2C%20V.S.%20Seigell%20and%20S.S.%20Dhanoa%20were%20appointed%20as%20ECs.%20It%20was%20for%20the%20first%20time%20after%20Independence%20that%20ECs%20were%20appointed%2C%20thereby%20making%20the%20ECI%20a%20multi-member%20commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20January%201%2C%201990%2C%20the%20President%20of%20India%20issued%20two%20notifications%20%E2%80%93%20one%20rescinding%2C%20with%20immediate%20effect%2C%20the%20notification%20of%20October%207%2C%201989%20creating%20the%20two%20posts%20of%20ECs%20and%20another%20rescinding%2C%20with%20immediate%20effect%2C%20the%20notification%20of%20October%2016%2C%201989%2C%20by%20which%20the%20appointment%20of%20S.S.%20Dhanoa%20and%20V.S.%20Seigell%20was%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDhanao%20unsuccessfully%20challenged%20these%20two%20notifications%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fjonew%2Fjudis%2F30335.pdf%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ES.S.%20Dhanoa%20versus%20Union%20of%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20rejected%20the%20petition%20by%20Dhanao%20holding%20that%20the%20creation%20and%20abolition%20of%20posts%20was%20the%20prerogative%20of%20the%20Executive%20and%20(in%20the%20present%20case)%20of%20the%20President%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20further%20held%20that%20Article%20324(2)%20leaves%20it%20to%20the%20President%20of%20India%20to%20fix%20and%20appoint%20such%20a%20number%20of%20ECs%20as%20he%20may%20from%20time%20to%20time%20determine.%20The%20power%20to%20create%20the%20posts%20is%20unfettered.%20So%20also%20is%20the%20power%20to%20reduce%20or%20abolish%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%C2%A0Parliament%20passed%20an%20Act%20titled%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bareactslive.com%2FACA%2FACT1510.HTM%3FAspxAutoDetectCookieSupport%3D1%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20other%20Commissioners.%20(Conditions%20of%20Service)%20Act%2C%201991%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20regulate%20conditions%20of%20service%20of%20CECs%20and%20ECs.%20The%201991%20Act%20came%20to%20be%20amended%20by%20an%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Frepealed-act%2Frepealed_act_documents%2FA1994-4.pdf%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOrdinance%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0published%20on%20October%201%2C%201993.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20October%201%2C%201993%2C%20the%20President%20again%20issued%20a%20notification%20fixing%20the%20number%20of%20ECs%20other%20than%20the%20CEC%20at%20two%20until%20further%20orders.%20Two%20ECs%2C%C2%A0M.S.%20Gill%20and%20G.V.G.%20Krishnamurthy%2C%20were%20appointed%20with%20effect%20from%20October%201%2C%201993.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-elementor-type%3D%5C%22section%5C%22%20data-elementor-id%3D%5C%2238796%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Csection%20data-id%3D%5C%222c9dbb0%5C%22%20data-element_type%3D%5C%22section%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-id%3D%5C%22bbfa45f%5C%22%20data-element_type%3D%5C%22column%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-id%3D%5C%22cbb21ab%5C%22%20data-widget_type%3D%5C%22posts.custom%5C%22%20data-element_type%3D%5C%22widget%5C%22%20data-settings%3D%5C%22%7B%26quot%3Bcustom_columns%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3B1%26quot%3B%2C%26quot%3Bcustom_row_gap%26quot%3B%3A%7B%26quot%3Bunit%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3Bpx%26quot%3B%2C%26quot%3Bsize%26quot%3B%3A0%2C%26quot%3Bsizes%26quot%3B%3A%5B%5D%7D%2C%26quot%3Bcustom_columns_tablet%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3B2%26quot%3B%2C%26quot%3Bcustom_columns_mobile%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3B1%26quot%3B%2C%26quot%3Bcustom_row_gap_tablet%26quot%3B%3A%7B%26quot%3Bunit%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3Bpx%26quot%3B%2C%26quot%3Bsize%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3B%26quot%3B%2C%26quot%3Bsizes%26quot%3B%3A%5B%5D%7D%2C%26quot%3Bcustom_row_gap_mobile%26quot%3B%3A%7B%26quot%3Bunit%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3Bpx%26quot%3B%2C%26quot%3Bsize%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3B%26quot%3B%2C%26quot%3Bsizes%26quot%3B%3A%5B%5D%7D%7D%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-settings%3D%5C%22%7B%26quot%3Bcurrent_page%26quot%3B%3A1%2C%26quot%3Bmax_num_pages%26quot%3B%3A0%2C%26quot%3Bload_method%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3B%26quot%3B%2C%26quot%3Bwidget_id%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3Bcbb21ab%26quot%3B%2C%26quot%3Bpost_id%26quot%3B%3A56168%2C%26quot%3Btheme_id%26quot%3B%3A38796%2C%26quot%3Bchange_url%26quot%3B%3Afalse%2C%26quot%3Breinit_js%26quot%3B%3Afalse%7D%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3EThe%20amendment%20and%20the%20appointments%20came%20to%20be%20challenged%20by%20T.N.%20Seshan%2C%20the%20then%20CEC%20and%20others.%20A%20Constitution%20Bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1890680%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ET.N.%20Seshan%2C%20Chief%20Election%20Commr.%20of%20India%20versus%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20rejected%20the%20challenge.%3Cb%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fsection%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bench%20observed%20that%20the%C2%A0concept%20of%20plurality%20was%20writ%20large%20on%20the%20face%20of%20Article%20324%2C%20Clause%20(2)%20whereof%20clearly%20envisages%20a%20multi-member%20election%20commission%20comprising%20a%20CEC%20and%20one%20or%20more%20ECs.%20If%20a%20multi-member%20election%20commission%20was%20not%20contemplated%2C%20where%20was%20the%20need%20to%20provide%20in%20clause%20(3)%20for%20the%20CEC%20to%20act%20as%20its%20chairman%2C%20the%20Bench%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%2C%20therefore%2C%20no%20room%20for%20doubt%20that%20the%20ECI%20could%20be%20a%20multi-member%20body%2C%20the%20Bench%20held.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20had%20multi-member%20election%20commissions%20in%20operation%20since%201993%2C%20with%20decision-making%20power%20by%20majority%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%3E%3Cb%3ESupreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20intervention%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%202%20last%20year%2C%20a%20Constitution%20Bench%20comprising%20Justices%20K.M.%20Joseph%2C%20Ajay%20Rastogi%2C%20Aniruddha%20Bose%2C%20Hrishikesh%20Roy%20and%20C.T.%20Ravikumar%20had%3Ca%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22internal%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fcollegium-for-election-commission-members-supreme-court-takes-away-governments-powers%2F%5C%22%3E%C2%A0held%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20the%20appointment%20of%20CECs%20and%20ECs%20would%20be%20on%20the%20recommendation%20of%20a%3Ca%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22internal%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fexplaining-election-commission-of-india-ruling-supreme-court-checks-executives-power-to-appoint-members-calls-for-balance%2F%5C%22%3E%C2%A0committee%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0consisting%20of%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20(CJI)%2C%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20and%20the%20Leader%20of%20the%20Opposition%20in%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bench%20believed%20that%20the%20ECI%20had%20to%20perform%20the%20arduous%20and%20unenviable%20task%20of%20remaining%20aloof%20from%20all%20forms%20of%20subjugation%20by%20and%20interference%20from%20the%20Executive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EParliament%20undid%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20ruling%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMonths%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20ruling%2C%20the%20Parliament%20enacted%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fhandle%2F123456789%2F19721%3Fview_type%3Dbrowse%26sam_handle%3D123456789%2F1362%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20other%20Election%20Commissioners%20(Appointment%2C%20Conditions%20of%20Service%20and%20Term%20of%20Office)%20Act%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20Act%20has%20dropped%20the%20CJI%20from%20the%20selection%20committee%20to%20appoint%20a%20CEC%20and%20ECs.%20The%20selection%20committee%20under%20the%20new%20law%20to%20appoint%20a%20CEC%20and%20ECs%20provides%20the%20Executive%20a%20two-third%20voting%20majority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20also%20provides%20that%20a%20CEC%20and%20other%20ECs%20be%20appointed%20from%20amongst%20persons%20who%20are%20holding%20or%20have%20held%20a%20post%20equivalent%20to%20the%20rank%20of%20secretary%20to%20the%20government%20of%20India%20and%20who%20are%20persons%20of%20integrity%20with%20knowledge%20of%20and%20experience%20in%20the%20management%20and%20conduct%20of%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20new%20law%2C%20the%20search%20committee%20headed%20by%20the%20minister%20of%20law%20and%20justice%20and%20comprising%20two%20other%20members%20not%20below%20the%20rank%20of%20secretary%20to%20the%20government%20of%20India%20shall%20prepare%20a%20panel%20of%20five%20persons%20for%20consideration%20of%20the%20selection%20committee%2C%20for%20appointment%20as%20a%20CEC%20and%20other%20ECs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThereafter%2C%20a%20panel%20comprising%20the%20Prime%20Minister%3B%20the%20Leader%20of%20Opposition%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20a%20Union%20cabinet%20minister%20to%20be%20nominated%20by%20the%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20shall%20recommend%20the%20name%20for%20the%20appointment%20to%20be%20made%20by%20the%20President.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Act%20also%20provides%20that%20a%20CEC%20and%20ECs%20shall%20hold%20office%20for%20a%20term%20of%20six%20years%20from%20the%20date%20on%20which%20they%20assume%20office%20or%20till%20they%20attain%20the%20age%20of%20sixty-five%20years%2C%20whichever%20is%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20clarifies%20that%20when%20an%20EC%20is%20appointed%20as%20the%20CEC%2C%20his%20term%20of%20office%20shall%20not%20be%20more%20than%20six%20years%20in%20aggregate.%20CECs%20and%20ECs%20shall%20not%20be%20eligible%20for%20re-appointment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%3E%3Cb%3EDifferent%20yardstick%20for%20removal%20of%20CEC%20and%20EC%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20Article%20324(5)%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20a%20CEC%C2%A0shall%20not%20be%20removed%20from%20his%20office%20except%20in%20like%20manner%20and%20on%20the%20like%20grounds%20as%20a%20judge%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20the%20conditions%20of%20service%20of%20a%20CEC%20shall%20not%20be%20varied%20to%20his%20disadvantage%20after%20his%20appointment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20removal%20of%20ECs%2C%20the%20Constitution%20provides%20that%20they%20shall%20not%20be%20removed%20from%20office%20except%20on%20the%20recommendation%20of%20the%20CEC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Parliament%20in%20the%202023%20Act%20also%20codified%20the%20same%20notwithstanding%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20observation%20in%20its%20March%202023%20ruling%20that%20it%20was%C2%A0desirable%20that%20the%20grounds%20of%20removal%20of%20the%20ECs%20shall%20be%20the%20same%20as%20that%20of%20the%20CEC%2C%20that%20is%2C%20on%20like%20grounds%20as%20a%20judge%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20subject%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Erecommendation%20of%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D%20as%20provided%20under%20the%20second%20proviso%20to%20Article%20324(5)%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India.%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fexplained-on-arun-goels-resignation-what-is-the-law-on-appointment-and-termination-of-services-of-election-commissioners%2F%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20first%20appeared%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20Leaflet%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710156729000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15125309%2FNirvachan-Sadan-TW.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Farun-goels-resignation-what-is-the-established-law-on-the-appointment-of-election-commissioners%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20has%20had%20multi-member%20election%20commissions%20in%20operation%20since%201993%2C%20with%20decision-making%20power%20by%20majority%20vote.%20With%20Arun%20Goel's%20resignation%20as%20election%20commissioner%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20has%20been%20reduced%20to%20one-man%20commission.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Farun-goels-resignation-what-is-the-established-law-on-t