%20%E2%80%94%20over%20the%20next%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhospitals-are-facing-economic-turmoil-in-the-coronavirus-pandemic-2020-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehospitals%20are%20teetering%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20brink.%20In%202022%2C%20Conemaugh%20Nason%20Medical%20Center%20in%20Pennsylvania%20announced%20it%20was%20ending%20OB-GYN%20deliveries%2C%20leaving%20some%20mothers-to-be%20to%20travel%20almost%20an%20hour%20to%20give%20birth.%20Last%20year%2C%20Glenwood%20Regional%20Medical%20Center%20in%20Louisiana%20was%20ordered%20by%20the%20state%20to%20turn%20away%20patients%20because%20of%20inadequate%20supplies%20and%20staffing%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20their%20financial%20struggles%2C%20all%20of%20the%20hospitals%20shared%20three%20things%20in%20common.%20They%20all%20served%20low-income%20communities%20that%20suffered%20from%20a%20lack%20of%20access%20to%20healthcare.%20They%20were%20all%20owned%20at%20various%20points%20by%20for-profit%20investors%2C%20including%20leading%20private-equity%20firms%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-family-rental-investors-squeeze-regular-homebuyers-cerberus-invitation-homes-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECerberus%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-equity-industry-investing-lessons-from-john-danhakl-of-leonard-green-2019-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELeonard%20Green%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-equity-salaries-at-blackstone-apollo-kkr-bain-others%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApollo%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20in%20a%20move%20that%20stripped%20the%20hospitals%20of%20one%20of%20their%20prime%20assets%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20owners%20had%20sold%20the%20land%20beneath%20the%20facilities%20to%20a%20little-known%20real-estate%20investor%20called%20Medical%20Properties%20Trust.%20MPT%2C%20which%20has%20purchased%20some%20%2416%20billion%20of%20hospital%20real%20estate%20over%20the%20past%20two%20decades%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalpropertiestrust.com%2Fcompany%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enow%20bills%20itself%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20largest%20owners%20of%20hospital%20beds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20of%20the%20hospitals%2C%20the%20deals%20proved%20disastrous.%20Once%20their%20real%20estate%20was%20sold%20to%20MPT%2C%20they%20were%20forced%20to%20pay%20rent%20on%20what%20had%20always%20been%20their%20own%20property.%20That%20added%20to%20the%20massive%20debt%20burdens%20already%20placed%20on%20the%20hospitals%20by%20their%20for-profit%20owners%2C%20deepening%20their%20financial%20woes.%20It%20also%20deprived%20Americans%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhospitals-struggling-keep-up-with-covid-19-surge-in-cases-2020-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edesperately%20needed%20healthcare%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20put%20lives%20at%20risk%20%E2%80%94%20all%20while%20enriching%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esome%20of%20the%20world's%20wealthiest%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221900%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Northside%20Regional%20Medical%20Center%20in%20Ohio%20abandoned.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e78c5d6080194819fcd0bb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENorthside%20Regional%20Medical%20Center%20in%20Ohio%20was%20forced%20to%20shut%20down%20after%20its%20land%20was%20sold%20to%20MPT.%3Cp%3ESherman%20Cahal%2F%20Abandoned%20Online%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20biggest%20scam%20that%20almost%20no%20one%20knows%20about%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Rob%20Simone%2C%20a%20researcher%20at%20the%20risk-management%20firm%20Hedgeye%20who%20has%20spent%20hundreds%20of%20hours%20digging%20through%20MPT's%20financial%20filings%20and%20business%20dealings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWrit%20large%2C%20MPT's%20hospital%20investments%20represent%20a%20breathtaking%20scheme%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethat%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-surgeon-general-medical-bill-shows-broken-healthcare-system-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edecimated%20healthcare%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20communities%20across%20America.%20And%20while%20the%20legal%20universe%20is%20not%20the%20same%20as%20the%20moral%20one%20%E2%80%94%20despicable%20actions%2C%20such%20as%20getting%20rich%20by%20cutting%20off%20care%20to%20the%20poor%2C%20can%20be%20perfectly%20legal%20%E2%80%94%20MPT's%20deals%20underscore%20how%20giant%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-street-private-equity-woes-debt-stock-market-interest-rates-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprivate-equity%20firms%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20profited%20while%20gutting%20a%20critical%20piece%20of%20America's%20infrastructure%2C%20even%20on%20deals%20that%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsafety-net-hospitals-worry-funding-shortfall-coronavirus-stimulus-2020-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinancial%20catastrophes%20for%20the%20hospitals%20and%20their%20communities%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20told%2C%20at%20least%2013%20hospitals%20have%20closed%20or%20gone%20bankrupt%20after%20their%20land%20was%20sold%20to%20MPT.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAnd%20the%20damage%20is%20far%20from%20over.%20In%20January%2C%20MPT%20reported%20that%20its%20biggest%20tenant%2C%20a%20nationwide%20chain%20of%2032%20hospitals%20called%20Steward%2C%20could%20no%20longer%20pay%20its%20rent.%20The%20announcement%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0which%20has%20left%20health%20officials%20scrambling%20for%20fallback%20plans%20to%20provide%20care%20to%20the%202.2%20million%20people%20served%20by%20Steward%20%E2%80%94%20could%20foreshadow%20more%20hospital%20closings%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMPT%20existed%20to%20allow%20private%20equity%20to%20take%20money%20out%20of%20our%20hospital%20system%20through%20uneconomic%20transactions%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Justin%20Simon%2C%20who%20runs%20a%20successful%20healthcare-focused%20hedge%20fund%20called%20Jasper%20Capital.%20%26quot%3BNow%20they've%20bankrupted%20the%20hospitals.%20The%20communities%20are%20left%20holding%20the%20bag%2C%20and%20no%20one%20is%20going%20to%20jail.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EMPT%20was%20founded%20in%202003%20by%20Ed%20Aldag%2C%20an%20Alabama%20native%20who%20serves%20as%20the%20firm's%20president%2C%20chairman%2C%20and%20CEO.%20The%20core%20idea%20was%20simple%3A%20to%20buy%20hospital%20real%20estate%2C%20pocket%20the%20lease%20payments%2C%20and%20use%20the%20money%20to%20reward%20investors.%20(By%20law%2C%20real-estate%20investment%20trusts%20like%20MPT%20must%20pay%2090%25%20of%20their%20taxable%20income%20to%20shareholders.)%20Over%20the%20past%20few%20decades%2C%20plenty%20of%20private-equity%20firms%20have%20engaged%20in%20a%20similar%20form%20of%20financial%20engineering%2C%20called%20sale-leasebacks%2C%20with%20hotels%20and%20retailers.%20Selling%20the%20real%20estate%20was%20a%20key%20element%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20of%20the%20financier%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsears-avoids-liquidation-bankruptcy-2019-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEddie%20Lampert's%20plan%20to%20make%20money%20from%20a%20struggling%20Sears%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20no%20one%20had%20done%20it%20at%20a%20massive%20scale%20with%20hospitals%20%E2%80%94%20for%20reasons%2C%20perhaps%2C%20that%20should%20have%20been%20obvious.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMPT%20came%20along%20at%20the%20perfect%20moment.%20Hospitals%20in%20rural%20and%20underserved%20communities%20have%20always%20been%20a%20tough%20business%2C%20for%20the%20simple%20reason%20that%20they%20serve%20more%20patients%20who%20are%20uninsured%20or%20who%20rely%20on%20Medicaid%2C%20which%20reimburses%20at%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20rate%20of%20commercial%20insurance.%20But%20then%20two%20things%20happened.%20First%2C%20in%202006%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiger-global-venture-capital-bain-relationship-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBain%20Capital%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20handful%20of%20other%20investors%20bought%20the%20massive%20hospital%20chain%20HCA%20and%20quickly%20made%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pehub.com%2Fwith-hca-ipo-bain-kkr-and-baml-could-triple-their-money-on-paper-anyway%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efortune%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Second%2C%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20Affordable%20Care%20Act%20in%202010%20added%20to%20the%20gold-rush%20mentality%20by%20promising%20to%20dramatically%20expand%20the%20number%20of%20Americans%20with%20insurance%2C%20thereby%20improving%20hospital%20margins.%20By%202011%2C%20seven%20of%20the%20nation's%20top%20for-profit%20chains%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ineteconomics.org%2Fperspectives%2Fblog%2Fprivate-equity-buyouts-in-healthcare-who-wins-who-loses%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eowned%20by%20private-equity%20firms%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20say%20the%20investments%20didn't%20pan%20out%20would%20be%20an%20understatement.%20Obamacare%20didn't%20wind%20up%20providing%20the%20expected%20infusion%20of%20cash%2C%20and%20the%20government%20has%20continued%20to%20slash%20Medicaid%20reimbursements.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20hospitals%20in%20rural%20and%20underserved%20areas%20continued%20to%20be%20a%20difficult%20business%20proposition%2C%20and%20their%20private-equity%20investors%20were%20facing%20serious%20losses.%20%26quot%3BThe%20hospital%20chains%20faced%20major%20challenges%20in%20meeting%20loan%20obligations%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20economist%20Eileen%20Appelbaum%20and%20Rosemary%20Batt%2C%20a%20management%20professor%20at%20Cornell%20University%2C%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20capitalism%20worked%20the%20way%20it's%20supposed%20to%2C%20that%20would%20have%20been%20the%20end%20of%20the%20story.%20Investors%20make%20a%20bet%2C%20it%20goes%20sideways%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Evoil%C3%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20they%20lose%20their%20money.%20But%20in%20this%20case%2C%20private-equity%20firms%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efound%20a%20new%20way%20to%20save%20their%20failed%20investments%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%E2%80%94%20by%20selling%20the%20land%20under%20the%20hospitals%20to%20MPT.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%2C%20which%20didn't%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%2C%20has%20insisted%20the%20deals%20are%20good%20for%20hospitals%20as%20well%20as%20investors%2C%20because%20they%20inject%20much-needed%20cash%20into%20underfunded%20systems.%20%26quot%3BWe%20provide%20up%20to%20100%25%20of%20a%20hospital's%20real%20estate%20value%20to%20help%20fund%20facility%20expansions%2C%20investments%20in%20people%20and%20technology%2C%20and%20the%20execution%20of%20long-term%20growth%20strategies%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalpropertiestrust.com%2Fcapabilities%23%3A~%3Atext%3DMPT%2520UNLOCKS%2520CAPITAL%2520FOR%2520GROWTH%26amp%3Btext%3DWe%2520provide%2520up%2520to%2520100%2Cworld%2520with%2520our%2520capital%2520solutions.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMTP%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20on%20its%20website.%20%26quot%3BUltimately%2C%20we%20help%20hospitals%20serve%20patients%20better%20around%20the%20world%20with%20our%20capital%20solutions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrivate-equity%20firms%20tell%20the%20same%20story.%20In%20statements%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Cerberus%2C%20Apollo%2C%20and%20Leonard%20Green%20said%20none%20of%20the%20money%20from%20the%20MTP%20deals%20was%20distributed%20to%20shareholders.%20Instead%2C%20they%20said%2C%20the%20funds%20benefited%20the%20hospitals%20by%20enabling%20them%20to%20do%20things%20like%20improve%20their%20facilities%2C%20pay%20down%20their%20debts%2C%20provide%20benefits%20to%20their%20employees%2C%20and%20extend%20free%20care%20to%20their%20communities.%20The%20firms%20also%20insisted%20that%20their%20decisions%20left%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20hospitals%20in%20strong%20financial%20health.%20Leonard%20Green%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20said%20that%20when%20it%20exited%20its%20investment%20in%20a%20hospital%20system%20called%20Prospect%20in%202021%2C%20the%20company%20had%20%26quot%3Baccess%20to%20over%20a%20half%20billion%20dollars%20to%20support%20its%20operation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224058%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Marc%20Rowan%2C%20CEO%20of%20Apollo%20Global%20Management%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e79eb2ce7f1785b2e6a8b4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223043%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMarc%20Rowan%2C%20CEO%20of%20Apollo%2C%20which%20owns%20220%20hospitals%20across%2036%20states.%20%3Cp%3ENurPhoto%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20wherever%20the%20funds%20from%20the%20MPT%20transactions%20were%20placed%20on%20the%20books%2C%20the%20deals%20saddled%20the%20hospitals%20with%20years%20of%20rent%20payments%2C%20contributing%20to%20their%20financial%20struggles.%20And%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20deals%2C%20private-equity%20firms%20wound%20up%20getting%20rich%20off%20investments%20that%2C%20by%20any%20rational%20measure%2C%20should%20have%20been%20failures%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0often%20by%20paying%20themselves%20and%20their%20investors%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehefty%20dividends.%20%26quot%3BI%20estimate%20that%20less%20than%2010%25%20of%20the%20money%20has%20actually%20been%20reinvested%20into%20the%20hospital%20systems%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Richard%20Mortell%2C%20the%20managing%20partner%20of%20Third%20Coast%20Real%20Estate%20Capital%2C%20who%20has%20studied%20MPT's%20deals.%20%26quot%3BThe%20vast%20majority%20was%20either%20distributed%20to%20owners%2C%20or%20used%20to%20repay%20debt%20taken%20out%20to%20distribute%20money%20to%20owners.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-private-equity-firms-cash-in-on-struggling-retailers-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPrivate-equity%20investors%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20long%20turned%20a%20profit%20by%20saddling%20the%20companies%20they%20buy%20with%20massive%20debt%2C%20even%20if%20it%20means%20running%20the%20businesses%20into%20the%20ground.%20But%20with%20MPT%2C%20what%20started%20out%20as%20a%20way%20to%20rescue%20a%20failed%20investment%20strategy%20wound%20up%20creating%20a%20whole%20new%20form%20of%20financial%20engineering%20for%20private-equity%20profiteers.%20Firms%20like%20Apollo%2C%20Cerberus%2C%20and%20Leonard%20Green%20couldn't%20make%20money%20by%20selling%20their%20debt-laden%20hospitals%20back%20to%20the%20public%20markets%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they%20could%20exploit%20the%20value%20of%20the%20underlying%20real%20estate.%20In%20the%20process%2C%20they%20stuck%20the%20struggling%20hospitals%20with%20something%20they'd%20never%20had%20before%2C%20and%20couldn't%20afford%20to%20pay%3A%20rent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EMPT's%20biggest%20deals%20have%20been%20with%20Cerberus%2C%20the%20secretive%20financial%20colossus%20run%20by%20Stephen%20Feinberg%2C%20a%20billionaire%20whose%20investments%20in%20gun%20companies%20have%20been%20the%20subject%20of%20much%20controversy.%20It%20all%20began%20in%202010%2C%20when%20Cerberus%20acquired%20a%20struggling%20nonprofit%20hospital%20system%20and%20rebranded%20it%20as%20for-profit%20Steward%20Health%20Care.%20Steward's%20CEO%2C%20a%20charismatic%20doctor%20named%20Ralph%20de%20la%20Torre%2C%20talked%20a%20big%20game%20about%20fixing%20healthcare%20in%20marginalized%20communities.%20In%20announcing%20the%20deal%2C%20Cerberus%20assured%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pressreader.com%2Fusa%2Fthe-boston-globe%2F20240123%2F281513641022244%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Boston%20Globe%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Ba%20big%20win%20for%20the%20hard-working%20communities%20of%20Greater%20Boston.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EState%20regulators%20were%20suspicious%20of%20the%20deal.%20In%20return%20for%20state%20approval%2C%20Steward%20promised%20it%20wouldn't%20add%20any%20debt%20to%20the%20hospitals%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20paying%20Cerberus%20a%20dividend%20or%20distribution%20for%20three%20years.%20As%20it%20turned%20out%2C%20regulators%20weren't%20suspicious%20enough%3A%20They%20didn't%20foresee%20MPT.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%202016%20to%202022%2C%20according%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedicalpropertiestrust.gcs-web.com%2Fstatic-files%2F9f32b6d4-5210-424c-b110-4f40a787a93d%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20a%20company%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20MPT%20acquired%20a%20net%20%243.3%20billion%20of%20real%20estate%20underlying%2034%20Steward%20facilities.%20MPT%20then%20leased%20the%20real%20estate%20back%20to%20Steward.%20The%20deal%20was%20done%20to%20%26quot%3Bgive%20Cerberus%20some%20liquidity%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Brecover%20the%20original%20investment%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20an%20announcement%20at%20the%20time.%20Steward%20now%20has%20an%20annual%20rent%20burden%20of%20almost%20%24400%20million%2C%20according%20to%20Simone%2C%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20which%20goes%20to%20MPT.%20In%20the%20process%2C%20Steward%20became%20MPT's%20largest%20tenant%2C%20at%20one%20point%20accounting%20for%20as%20much%20as%2030%25%20of%20its%20annual%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20MPT%20deal%2C%20Cerberus%20made%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20from%20its%20investment%20in%20Steward.%20According%20to%20a%20confidential%20investor%20document%20acquired%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Ffeatures%2F2020-08-06%2Fcerberus-backed-hospitals-face-life-and-debt-as-virus-rages%3Fsref%3D6y0OF8u2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20one%20of%20Cerberus'%20funds%20collected%20a%20dividend%20of%20%24484%20million.%20Overall%2C%20Steward's%20investors%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2021-05-27%2Fcerberus-quadruples-money-after-unusual-exit-from-hospital-giant%3Fsref%3D6y0OF8u2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20quadrupled%20their%20money%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20even%20as%20the%20hospitals%20themselves%20were%20hemorrhaging%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223900%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Medics%20transfer%20a%20patient%20on%20a%20stretcher%20from%20an%20ambulance%20outside%20of%20Emergency%20at%20Coral%20Gables%20Hospital%20where%20Coronavirus%20patients%20are%20treated%20in%20Coral%20Gables%20near%20Miami%2C%20on%20July%2030%2C%202020.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e8e6c06080194819fd595c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222596%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EInvestors%20in%20Steward%20quadrupled%20their%20money.%20The%20hospitals%20are%20now%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20collapse.%3Cp%3EChandan%20Khanna%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCerberus%20generated%20a%20home-run%20multiple%20on%20an%20unsuccessful%20investment%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Mortell%2C%20the%20longtime%20real-estate%20investor.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20the%20way%20capitalism%20is%20supposed%20to%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20to%20BI%2C%20Cerberus%20said%20its%20involvement%20with%20Steward%20enabled%20the%20chain%20to%20invest%20%24800%20million%20on%20infrastructure%2C%20technology%2C%20and%20personnel%2C%20transforming%20its%20failing%20hospitals%20into%20%26quot%3Ba%20world-class%20accountable%20care%20organization.%26quot%3B%20But%20Steward%20didn't%20exactly%20thrive%20after%20its%20purchase%20by%20Cerberus.%20One%20after%20another%2C%20many%20of%20the%20chain's%20hospitals%20have%20either%20closed%20or%20been%20forced%20to%20cut%20services.%20During%20the%20pandemic%2C%20Easton%20Hospital%20in%20Pennsylvania%20received%20a%20last-minute%20bailout%20from%20the%20state%20after%20Steward%20threatened%20to%20close%20it.%20Local%20leaders%20were%20incensed.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20to%20believe%20that%20Easton%20Hospital%20could%20have%20sat%20vacant%20in%20the%20coming%20months%20%E2%80%94%20shedding%20700%20jobs%20in%20the%20process%20%E2%80%94%20as%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20Lehigh%20Valley%20scurried%20to%20free%20up%20every%20room%2C%20ventilator%2C%20and%20medical%20staffer%20to%20try%20to%20save%20lives%2C%26quot%3B%20fumed%20the%20local%20newspaper's%20editorial%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20more%2C%20Steward%20has%20been%20sued%20by%20a%20handful%20of%20vendors%20for%20leaving%20what%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20trail%20of%20unpaid%20bills.%20In%20January%2C%20at%20St.%20Elizabeth's%20Medical%20Center%20in%20Boston%2C%20a%20new%20mother%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bostonglobe.com%2F2024%2F01%2F25%2Fbusiness%2Fsteward-health-care-mother-death%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebled%20to%20death%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20a%20device%20that%20could%20have%20saved%20her%20life%20had%20been%20repossessed%20by%20creditors%20because%20Steward%20had%20failed%20to%20pay%20the%20bill.%20Now%2C%20the%20hospital%20chain's%20looming%20collapse%20could%20endanger%20even%20more%20lives%2C%20most%20of%20them%20in%20poor%20communities.%20%26quot%3BThe%20burden%20of%20Steward%20hospital%20closures%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.boston.com%2Fnews%2Fhealth%2F2024%2F01%2F24%2Flawmakers-answers-steward-hospital-financial-difficulties%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eletter%3C%2Fa%3E%20signed%20by%20the%20state's%20entire%20congressional%20delegation%20warned%2C%20%26quot%3Bwould%20be%20borne%20primarily%20by%20the%20Massachusetts%20residents%20who%20already%20experience%20the%20greatest%20challenges%20accessing%20health%20care.%26quot%3B%20The%20delegation%20has%20asked%20Cerberus%20to%20provide%20details%20of%20its%20investment%20in%20Steward%2C%20including%20how%20much%20money%20it%20extracted%20from%20the%20chain.%20%26quot%3BThe%20net%20result%20of%20these%20transactions%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20delegation%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3Bappears%20to%20be%20an%20unfolding%20tragedy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20at%20Cerberus%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20aren't%20the%20only%20ones%20who%20scored%20a%20home%20run%20by%20inflicting%20financial%20pain%20on%20Steward.%20In%202021%2C%20MPT%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sec.gov%2Fixviewer%2Fix.html%3Fdoc%3D%2FArchives%2Fedgar%2Fdata%2F0001287865%2F000156459022008100%2Fmpw-10k_20211231.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eloaned%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20hospital%20chain's%20operating%20team%2C%20including%20de%20la%20Torre%2C%20%24335%20million%20to%20buy%20out%20Cerberus.%20Steward%20then%20turned%20around%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprospect.org%2Fhealth%2F2023-05-23-quackonomics-medical-properties-trust%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20new%20owners%2C%20including%20de%20la%20Torre%2C%20a%20dividend%20of%20about%20%24100%20million.%20A%20few%20months%20later%2C%20de%20la%20Torre%20bought%20a%20%2440%20million%20yacht%20named%20the%20Amaral%2C%20which%20features%20a%20library%2C%20a%20gym%2C%20and%20a%20whirlpool%20on%20the%20top%20deck.%20Just%20after%20that%2C%20Steward%20filed%20with%20the%20government%20to%20delay%20paying%20back%20pandemic-era%20loans%2C%20citing%20%26quot%3Bextreme%20financial%20hardship.%26quot%3B%20(Steward%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221968%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ralph%20de%20la%20Torre%20and%20yacht.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e7974890413ab8e1d98953%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22984%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERalph%20de%20la%20Torre%2C%20CEO%20of%20Steward%2C%20bought%20a%20%2440%20million%20yacht%20after%20receiving%20a%20huge%20dividend%20from%20the%20struggling%20hospital%20chain.%3Cp%3EAnonymous%3B%20MediaNews%20Group%2FBoston%20Herald%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pattern%20of%20using%20MPT%20to%20profit%20from%20the%20pain%20of%20impoverished%20patients%20was%20repeated%20by%20other%20leading%20investors.%20Prospect%2C%20a%20chain%20of%20hospitals%20in%20underserved%20communities%2C%20was%20bought%20by%20Leonard%20Green%20in%202010.%20It%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20a%20bad%20investment.%20According%20to%20the%20Private%20Equity%20Stakeholder%20Project%2C%20a%20research%20and%20advocacy%20group%2C%20Prospect%20lost%20over%20%24600%20million%20between%202015%20and%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20in%202019%2C%20Leonard%20Green%20sold%20%241.55%20billion%20of%20Prospect's%20real%20estate%20to%20MPT.%20In%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Leonard%20Green%20said%20its%20ownership%20of%20the%20hospital%20chain%20%26quot%3Benabled%20Prospect%20to%20invest%20approximately%20%24750%20million%20in%20its%20hospitals%2C%20provide%20%24900%20million%20in%20free%20care%2C%20contribute%20%24170%20million%20to%20local%20taxes%2C%20and%20fund%20%24300%20million%20into%20employee%20pensions%20and%20401(k)%20plans.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20after%20Leonard%20Green%20sold%20off%20Prospect's%20real%20estate%2C%20the%20hospitals%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.propublica.org%2Farticle%2Finvestors-extracted-400-million-from-a-hospital-chain-that-sometimes-couldnt-pay-for-medical-supplies-or-gas-for-ambulances%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtinued%20to%20struggle%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Ambulances%20were%20unable%20to%20fuel%20up%20because%20their%20credit%20cards%20had%20been%20cut%20off.%20Elevators%20stopped%20working.%20Six%20elderly%20psychiatric%20patients%20with%20COVID-19%20died%20due%20to%20poor%20infection%20control.%20Yet%20the%20ownership%20group%20led%20by%20Leonard%20Green%2C%20the%20Stakeholder%20Project%20found%2C%20was%20somehow%20able%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpestakeholder.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F05%2FUPDATE-Leonard-Green-Prospect-Medical-Dividends-PESP-051420.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eextract%3C%2Fa%3E%20%24658%20million%20in%20dividends%20and%20other%20fees%20from%20the%20struggling%20hospital%20chain.%20Prospect%20is%20now%20attempting%20to%20sell%20three%20of%20its%20hospitals%20in%20Connecticut%20to%20Yale%20New%20Haven%20Health%20System%2C%20but%20the%20deal%20may%20fall%20through%20because%20of%20Prospect's%20mounting%20debt%20and%20unpaid%20bills.%20If%20Yale%20doesn't%20acquire%20the%20hospitals%2C%20they%20will%20likely%20go%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fctmirror.org%2F2023%2F12%2F14%2Fyale-prospect-medical-holdings-deal%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebankrupt%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20there%20are%20the%20deals%20that%20MPT%20has%20done%20with%20Apollo.%20In%202015%2C%20the%20private-equity%20giant%20bought%20its%20first%20hospital%20system%20and%20embarked%20on%20what's%20known%20as%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-rollout-a-roll-up-strategy-2012-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eroll-up%20strategy%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20popular%20play%20in%20which%20investors%20make%20a%20company%20bigger%2C%20though%20not%20necessarily%20better%2C%20by%20continuing%20to%20acquire%20businesses.%20The%20Apollo-backed%20business%20purchased%20several%20more%20healthcare%20companies%20and%20sold%20some%20of%20the%20underlying%20real%20estate%20%E2%80%94%20%24700%20million%20%E2%80%94%20to%20MPT.%20In%20a%20statement%20to%20BI%2C%20Apollo%20referred%20all%20questions%20about%20the%20deal%20to%20its%20hospital%20company%2C%20as%20if%20it%20had%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20the%20deals.%20But%20Aldag%2C%20the%20MPT%20founder%20and%20CEO%2C%20has%20boasted%20that%20the%20transactions%20were%20brokered%20directly%20with%20Apollo.%20%26quot%3BThey%20pretty%20much%20gave%20us%20their%20entire%20portfolio%20and%20said%2C%20'Here%2C%20pick%20what%20you'd%20like%20to%20have%20for%20this%20particular%20price%2C'%26quot%3B%20Aldag%20told%20investors%20in%20a%20conference%20call%20explaining%20the%20deal.%20Today%2C%20Apollo%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.beckershospitalreview.com%2Ffinance%2Fapollos-hospital-stranglehold-harms-patients-and-workers-report-alleges.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSince%2520acquiring%2520Lifepoint%2520in%25202018%2Cinvestigations%252C%2520according%2520to%2520the%2520report.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eowns%3C%2Fa%3E%20some%20220%20hospitals%20across%2036%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Apollo%20sold%20off%20their%20real%20estate%2C%20the%20hospitals%20continued%20to%20suffer.%20According%20to%20their%20financial%20statements%2C%20capital%20expenditures%20were%20less%20than%20depreciation%20in%20the%20years%20after%20the%20sale-leaseback%20deals%20with%20MPT%2C%20which%20means%20the%20asset%20base%20was%20being%20eroded%2C%20not%20increased.%20%26quot%3BApollo's%20hospital%20profiteering%20has%20resulted%20in%20dangerous%20conditions%2C%20closures%20and%20reduced%20access%20to%20services%2C%20and%20declining%20quality%2C%26quot%3B%20concluded%20Eileen%20O'Grady%2C%20a%20senior%20researcher%20at%20the%20Private%20Equity%20Stakeholder%20Project.%20Hospitals%20in%20one%20Apollo%20hospital%20chain%2C%20LifePoint%20Health%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpestakeholder.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FPESP__Report_Apollo_Lifepoint_2024.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erank%20among%20the%20worst%20in%20their%20states%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20Moody's%20has%20downgraded%20the%20company's%20debt%20to%20reflect%20the%20company's%20%26quot%3Belevated%20financial%20leverage.%26quot%3B%20Patients%20and%20communities%2C%20once%20again%2C%20paid%20the%20price%20for%20private%20equity's%20investment%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20real-estate%20deals%20with%20MPT%20have%20provided%20private-equity%20firms%20with%20a%20huge%20financial%20windfall%2C%20they've%20posed%20a%20problem%20for%20MPT%20itself.%20The%20more%20hospital%20real%20estate%20that%20MPT%20buys%2C%20the%20more%20money%20it%20makes%20in%20rent%20payments%20from%20the%20hospitals.%20But%20because%20its%20deals%20place%20huge%20financial%20stress%20on%20the%20hospitals%2C%20MPT%20is%20essentially%20operating%20as%20a%20landlord%20that%20is%20driving%20its%20own%20tenants%20out%20of%20business.%20Now%2C%20as%20hospital%20chains%20across%20the%20country%20find%20themselves%20unable%20to%20pay%20their%20rent%2C%20MPT%20is%20facing%20financial%20problems%20of%20its%20own.%20In%202020%2C%20its%20stock%20price%20hit%20%2424.%20Today%2C%20it's%20under%20%244.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20MPT's%20leaders%20didn't%20get%20rich%20off%20its%20hospital%20deals.%20Top%20executives%2C%20including%20Aldag%2C%20received%20hefty%20bonuses%20based%20in%20part%20on%20the%20dollar%20volume%20of%20transactions%20they%20did%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20the%20more%20hospitals%20they%20drove%20into%20debt%2C%20the%20better.%20Never%20mind%20that%2C%20as%20Simone%20found%2C%20MPT%20apparently%20used%20accounting%20assumptions%20that%20overinflated%20the%20lease%20payments%20it%20could%20realistically%20expect%20to%20receive%20from%20troubled%20hospital%20systems.%20From%202019%20to%202022%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.salary.com%2Ftools%2Fexecutive-compensation-calculator%2Fmedical-properties-trust-executive-salaries%3Fyear%3D2022%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESEC%20filings%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20MPT's%20top%20three%20executives%20were%20paid%20some%20%24125%20million%20in%20cash%20and%20equity%20grants.%20They%20got%20rich%2C%20in%20short%2C%20by%20making%20hospitals%20poor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%2C%20Congress%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.grassley.senate.gov%2Fnews%2Fnews-releases%2Fsenate-budget-committee-digs-into-impact-of-private-equity-ownership-in-americas-hospitals%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannounced%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20bipartisan%20investigation%20into%20private%20equity's%20influence%20in%20healthcare.%20MPT%20was%20included%20on%20the%20list%20of%20companies%20that%20received%20subpoenas.%20Sen.%20Chuck%20Grassley%2C%20the%20ranking%20Republican%20on%20the%20Senate%20Finance%20Committee%2C%20has%20asked%20Apollo%20and%20Leonard%20Green%20to%20submit%20details%20about%20its%20deals%20with%20MPT%2C%20among%20other%20things%3B%20the%20Massachusetts%20congressional%20delegation%20is%20asking%20Cerberus%20to%20account%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bostonglobe.com%2F2024%2F02%2F15%2Fbusiness%2Fsteward-private-equity-founders-massachusetts-congressional-delegation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhat%20happened%20at%20Steward%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20fundamental%20question%20is%3A%20Where%20did%20all%20the%20money%20go%3F%20If%20Congress%20does%20its%20job%20and%20follows%20the%20money%2C%20it%20may%20find%20itself%20confronting%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20financial%20heists%20in%20American%20history%20%E2%80%94%20one%20that%20transferred%20billions%20of%20dollars%20from%20needy%20patients%20to%20greedy%20investors.%20Lawmakers%20aren't%20empowered%20to%20get%20any%20of%20that%20money%20back.%20But%20they%20can%20at%20least%20make%20MPT%20and%20its%20private-equity%20partners%20account%20for%20what%20they%20got%20away%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fbethany-mc-lean%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EBethany%20McLean%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20special%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-wealthy-investors-got-rich-looting-needy-hospitals-healthcare-system-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710149161000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e74d2a6080194819fc94ca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-wealthy-investors-got-rich-looting-needy-hospitals-healthcare-system-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Inside%20the%20financial%20scheme%20that's%20crippling%20America's%20healthcare%20providers%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Bethany%20McLean)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-wealthy-investors-got-rich-looting-needy-hospitals-healthcare-system-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Watch%3A%20%E2%80%98Election%20Commission%20Image%20Damaged%20in%20Last%20Decade%2C%20Has%20to%20Prove%20Its%20Credibility%20by%20its%20Performance%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F11145016%2FKT-11-march-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20two%20separate%20interviews%20to%20discuss%20the%20Election%20Commission%2C%20at%20a%20time%20when%20it%20has%20been%20reduced%20to%20a%20one-man%20Commission%20and%20the%20prime%20minister%20has%20the%20power%20to%20overrule%20Opposition%20concerns%20whilst%20appointing%20two%20new%20election%20commissioners%2C%20two%20former%20chief%20election%20commissioners%20have%20expressed%20concern%20about%20the%20public%20image%20and%20impression%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ES.%20Y.%20Quraishi%20says%20the%20Election%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20image%20has%20been%20%E2%80%9Cdamaged%20a%20lot%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20last%20decade.%20He%20says%20%E2%80%9Cit%20worries%20me%20that%20the%20Election%20Commission%20has%20come%20into%20public%20criticism%E2%80%9D.%20He%20says%20it%20has%20failed%20to%20establish%20an%20arm%E2%80%99s%20length%20distance%20from%20the%20government.%20He%20says%20it%E2%80%99s%20guilty%20of%20lack%20of%20communication%20and%2C%20specifically%2C%20criticised%20the%20Commission%20for%20not%20meeting%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20separate%20interview%2C%20T.S.%20Krishnamurthy%20said%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Election%20Commission%20has%20to%20prove%20its%20credibility%20by%20its%20performance%E2%80%9D%20adding%20%E2%80%9Cit%20should%20not%20hesitate%20to%20correct%20the%20impression%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20free%20and%20fair%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20former%20chief%20election%20commissioners%20made%20clear%20that%20their%20preference%20would%20be%20a%20multi-member%20i.e.%20three%20member%20Election%20Commission%20but%20Quraishi%20added%20that%2C%20in%20principle%2C%20he%20has%20no%20problem%20with%20a%20one-man%20Commission%20and%20went%20on%20to%20specifically%20say%20that%20if%20that%20one%20man%20is%20the%20present%20CEC%2C%20Rajiv%20Kumar%2C%20he%20has%20complete%20faith%20in%20his%20integrity%20and%20competence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20former%20CECs%20also%20said%20they%20would%20prefer%20a%20collegium%20for%20choosing%20election%20commissioners%20which%20is%20not%20dominated%20by%20the%20government.%20Krishnamurthy%20specifically%20said%20he%20would%20have%20preferred%20the%20Collegium%20outlined%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20where%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20the%20chief%20justice%20and%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%20together%20choose%20election%20commissioners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20about%20the%20circumstances%20reported%20by%20newspapers%20surrounding%20the%20surprise%20resignation%20of%20Arun%20Goel%20%E2%80%93%20which%20are%20so%20far%20speculative%20and%20not%20confirmed%20%E2%80%93%20Krishnamurthy%20said%20%E2%80%9CI%20do%20not%20approve%20of%20a%20person%20straightaway%20resigning%E2%80%9D%20and%20he%20added%20%E2%80%9Cdifference%20of%20opinion%20is%20healthy%20and%20should%20continue%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20former%20chief%20election%20commissioners%20spoke%20about%20how%20in%20their%20time%20well-considered%20steps%20were%20taken%20to%20ensure%20that%20differences%20of%20opinion%20were%20resolved%20and%20not%20made%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FI-C3g47UaM0%3Fsi%3D4ns5xPZUpspTYohi%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710148896000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F11145016%2FKT-11-march-2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwatch-election-commission-image-damaged-in-last-decade-has-to-prove-its-credibility-by-its-performance%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Two%20former%20chief%20election%20commissioners%20have%20expressed%20concern%20about%20the%20public%20image%20and%20impression%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwatch-election-commission-image-damaged-in-last-decade-has-to-prove-its-credibility-by-its-performance%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BWell-Reasoned%26quot%3B%3A%20Top%20Court%20Declines%20Stay%20Ex-Professor%20Saibaba's%20Release%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ftopic%2FSupreme-Court%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Monday%20refused%20to%20stay%20the%20%26quot%3Bhard-earned%26quot%3B%20acquittal%20of%20ex-Delhi%20University%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ftopic%2Fgn-saibaba%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprofessor%20GN%20Saibaba%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20five%20others%2C%20all%20of%20whom%20had%20been%20accused%20of%20Maoist%20links%20and%20charged%20under%20stringent%20anti-terror%20law%20UAPA.%C2%A0The%20court%20also%20rejected%20an%20oral%20request%20by%20the%20Mahar